Script,EndplayStrip
window.currentPBSScenario = 'EndplayStrip';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Endplay_3rd_Round_Strip';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for EndplayStrip');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'EndplayStrip',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-DEFAULT
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1S
*/
predeal south SAK,CAJ
predeal north CK
predeal east  HQ

dealer south

# South opens 1S with 5-card spade suit, 14-17 HCP
sSpades = spades(south) > 4 and spades(south) < 6
sHcp    = hcp(south) > 13 and hcp(south) < 18
southHand = sSpades and sHcp

# North — 3-card support, 9-11 HCP
nSpades = spades(north) > 2 and spades(north) < 5
nHcp    = hcp(north) > 7 and hcp(north) < 12
northHand = nSpades and nHcp

# Q of clubs in opps (it's missing from declarer's side after predeal)
qClubInOpps = not hascard(south, QC) and not hascard(north, QC)

# Keep opps quiet
eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

southHand and northHand and qClubInOpps and eHcp and wHcp

action printoneline,
average "Q clubs with East " 100 * hascard(east, QC),
average "Q clubs with West " 100 * hascard(west, QC),
average "South HCP         "       hcp(south),
average "North HCP         "       hcp(north),
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Endplay / Strip,\n\
--- Strip-and-Endplay (4!S)\n\
South opens 1!S，partnership reaches 4!S.\n\
\n\
Teaching feature: declarer faces a critical loser problem in one side suit\n\
(typically clubs). Rather than finessing for the Q，declarer can STRIP the\n\
other suits，then throw East in with a heart and force East to lead into\n\
declarer's club tenace.\n\
\n\
Holdings:\n\
• Spades — 5-3 fit with solid honors.\n\
• Hearts — declarer has AKx (or similar) opposite small; can play two\n\
  rounds to exhaust East，then throw the third round to East.\n\
• Diamonds — declarer cashes A and K，ruffs the third in dummy if needed.\n\
• Clubs — AJx opposite Kxx，with the Q missing. The 50% finesse can be\n\
  avoided entirely by the endplay.\n\
\n\
The plan:\n\
1. Win the opening lead.\n\
2. Draw two rounds of trump (don't draw all — you may need a trump entry).\n\
3. Cash AK of diamonds; ruff the third diamond in dummy.\n\
4. Cash AK of hearts.\n\
5. Lead a third heart to East.\n\
6. East must return either a club (into your AJ tenace — J wins) or give\n\
   you a ruff-and-discard. Either way，you don't lose a club trick.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Why do you NOT take the club finesse?\n\
• What if East has shorter clubs than expected?\n\
• How do you keep the trumps you need to recover from each ruff?\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/endplay.php\n\
%EndplayStrip%
